<h3><a name="Next_meeting"></a> Next meeting </h3>
Fri Nov 16 at 2 pm CDT / 3 pm EDT
<p />
<h3><a name="Minutes_AN1"></a> Minutes </h3>
Deliverable of the group: document with a set of recommendations
<p />
<b>OIM AuthN: going over the documentation</b><br>
<a href="https://confluence.grid.iu.edu/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=4980895" target="_top">https://confluence.grid.iu.edu/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=4980895</a>
<p />
Can you limit yourself to 1 role? You can be authorized to take an action because you belong to multiple roles.<br>
You can have multiple DNs mapped to different roles. This is how developers would check new authorization schemes per role.
<p />
We would integrate OSG Dash with OIM for the OSG instance
<p />
Tom: can we use OIM from Struts?<br>
Soichi: yes, OIM is framework independent.
<p />
<b>grouper vs voms pros and cons</b>
<p />
Gabriele installed grouper and voms to prototype the dashboard AuthN API against real membership registration services.
<p />
Installation:<br>
grouper: straight forward after setting up java<br>
voms: x509 service certificate needed<br>
<p />
Trash/Trash/Integration with x509<br>
grouper: probably possible, no easily accessible docs on the web: need to contact the developers<br>
voms: supports x509 out of the box<br>
<p />
Do we want to support AuthN beyond x509?<br>
Possibly. Potential communities interested in the dashboard are a <span class="twikiNewLink">FrenchCloud<a href="/bin/edit/Documentation/FrenchCloud?topicparent=Documentation.NetworkingDashboardAuthNZGroup" rel="nofollow" title="FrenchCloud (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> and a UK cloud group.<br>
Do they have x509?<br>
If these groups have ties with the Grid, they may prefer VOMS.<br>
<p />
Strategy: we integrate OIM, then we have probably an API that can support both.
<p />
We need to discuss what the dashboard use cases actually are. How do you organize the data for the sites and resources? This will influence how to configure OIM at the MyOSG.<br>
If data belongs to a set of resources, it is a good fit for MyOSG<br>
MyOSG provides limited views in other systems, such as Gratia. It may provide a subset of the functionality of the Dashboard.<br>
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Group_meeting_Dec_6_2012"></a> Group meeting - Dec 6, 2012 </span></h2>
Present: Soichi, Gabriele, Tom, Parag, Shawn<br>
Date: Dec 6, 2012
<p />
<h3><a name="Action_Items_AN2"></a> Action Items </h3> <ul>
<li> Tom: Setting up the software in github <br>
</li> <li> Soichi: start prototype implementations for these use cases<br>
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h3><a name="Next_meeting_AN1"></a> Next meeting </h3>
Thu Jan 10 at 11 am CDT / 12 pm EDT
<p />
<h3><a name="Minutes_AN2"></a> Minutes </h3>
Discussion on old action items
<p />
<h4><a name="Use_cases"></a> Use cases </h4> <ul>
<li> Tom will provide use cases of interaction from the Dashboard to OIM
</li> <li> Soichi will evaluate if the use cases can be address by OIM as it or not
</li></ul> 
<p />
Tom: 3 types of components <ol>
<li> central data store: real authN needed here
</li> <li> the collector to run the probe
</li> <li> client
</li></ol> 
<p />
2 types of authN: <ol>
<li> collector: register number of IP from where request can come to run tests
</li> <li> client: with user id and password or x509
</li></ol> 
<p />
Soichi: we should be able to support these use cases
<p />
For the client we have 2 options: <ol>
<li> Client take client credentials and pass them to the data store; data store pass them to a policy decision point that returns yes/no. AuthN happens at this time every time.
</li> <li> Client talks to data store and data store gives a token, then later on it does not need AuthN anymore. Probably more complicated.
</li></ol> 
<p />
Soichi: generally implementing single-sign on as in (2). Typical for OIM.<br>
Tom: it may be harder for external developers to implement.<br>
Gabriele: we may be able to hide the complexity encapsulating it in an API for the client developers.<br>
<p />
Gabriele: For (1), we could use XACML call-out libraries as used in OSG.<br>
<p />
Soichi: Investigating issues with software licensing for version control system for data store and collector software. <br>
Shawn: OSG has accepted to put the code in github. Now interacting with github. <br>
Setting up all the pieces in github will be a challenge. <br>
Discussing organization of binary dependencies <br>
<p />
ACTION ITEM: Tom: Setting up the software in github. Probably 1 week.<br>
<p />
ACTION ITEM: Soichi: start prototype implementations for these use cases. Work on this in Dec.<br>
<p />
Parag: we use git with glidein WMS. Useful to maintain multiple branches. I'm willing to answer questions about git.
<p />
<h4><a name="Group_software"></a> Group software </h4>
All can try grouper and VOMS and see what is possible
<p />
Need to wait until we have something more concrete available.
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Group_meeting_Jan_10_2013"></a> Group meeting - Jan 10, 2013 </span></h2>
Present: Soichi, Gabriele, Tom, Rob Quick, Shawn<br>
Date: Jan 10, 2013
<p />
<h3><a name="Action_Items_AN3"></a> Action Items </h3> <ul>
<li> Tom will provide Soichi documentation on how to interact with the Data Store through the GUI.
</li> <li> Soichi: prototype authN/Z module
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h3><a name="Next_meeting_AN2"></a> Next meeting </h3>
Thu Feb 7 at 11 am CDT / 12 pm EDT
<p />
<h3><a name="Minutes_AN3"></a> Minutes </h3>
<p />
<i>Tom: Setting up the software in github</i><br>
github is ready. Uploaded code. Still need to put collector and GUI code: soon.<br>
Soichi has installed the code and it is working.
<p />
Tom will provide Soichi documentation on how to interact with the Data Store through the GUI.
<p />
<i>Soichi: start prototype implementations for these use cases</i><br>
Created 2 new instances on the ITB. Learning the system. Experimenting with the REST API of the Data Store.<br>
Next will work on the Collector and the UI.
<p />
Tom / Shawn: may need a 3rd machine for the GUI to separate it from the Data Store to keep the roles clean. This will be a source of the network information for the users. OSG will be a large installation, so we should think about scaling. It is also a test of our design<br>
Soichi: we can do that.<br>
<p />
We may have multiple UI implementations. Data Store needs to be protected using the AuthN/Z module, irrespectively of the UI used. <br>
We should NOT do AuthZ/N in the UI. It can be done as a filter in the Data Store. The UI sends the credentials to the Data Store and the Data Store interacts with the AuthN/Z module to define privileges. This way users can interact with the UI or directly with the Data Store.<br>
Soichi: it may be difficult to forward the credentials. The plan was for the UI to use its own password to access the store and UI to do the AuthN of the users. UI talks to OIM.<br>
Tom: The data store should be able to do AuthN/Z by its own, irrespectively of the UI.<br>
Soichi: OSG should not write data to the Data Store.<br>
Shwan: The collector should write to the Data Store, initially.<br>
<b>All: Data Store can have simple PASS/FAIL AuthZ. UI can do finer grain AuthZ</b><br>
Tom: worry is <span class="twikiNewLink">DoD<a href="/bin/edit/Documentation/DoD?topicparent=Documentation.NetworkingDashboardAuthNZGroup" rel="nofollow" title="DoD (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> from complex queries<br>
Soichi: we prefer an open system. We do not have a problem with Gratia.<br>
<p />
<b>Tom: we need to be able to AuthN/Z of the collectors</b><br>
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Group_meeting_Feb_7_2013"></a> Group meeting - Feb 7, 2013 </span></h2>
Present: Soichi, Gabriele, Parag, Tom, Shawn<br>
Date: Feb 7, 2013
<p />
<h3><a name="Action_Items_AN4"></a> Action Items </h3> <ul>
<li> Tom is working on finishing up the datastore (next week?). 
</li> <li> Soichi plans on learning more about the old dashboard and the current status of the existing development code. 
</li> <li> Tom will try to summarize what Lucy's code is doing and provide details in some new documentation he will add to the existing documentation.
</li> <li> Tom will send out the information when it is ready. 
</li> <li> Soichi will work on the GUI and prototype integration with OIM <span class="twikiNewLink">AuthN<a href="/bin/edit/Documentation/AuthN?topicparent=Documentation.NetworkingDashboardAuthNZGroup" rel="nofollow" title="AuthN (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>/Z
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h3><a name="Next_meeting_AN3"></a> Next meeting </h3>
At the OSG AHM
<p />
<h3><a name="Minutes_AN4"></a> Minutes </h3>
After Gabriele andd Parag left we talked about old dashboard and the new development work.  Tom sent out the URL for the old dashboard and one action item is for people to try to access it and then let Tom know via email. Tom can then add people with admin privileges.   The goal is to allow everyone to get a feel for what functionality exists in the old dashboard.  (The underlying code is NOT relevant...just the functionality it provides). 
URL is <a href="https://perfsonar.racf.bnl.gov:8443/exda/" target="_top">https://perfsonar.racf.bnl.gov:8443/exda/</a>
Create new hosts / services... don't change the existing configuration. The service is in use for CMS and Atlas.
<p />
Part of the discussion was on plans. 
Tom is working on finishing up the datastore (next week?). 
Soichi plans on learning more about the old dashboard and the current status of the existing development code. 
Tom will try to summarize what Lucy's code is doing and provide details in some new documentation he will add to the existing documentation.
Tom will send out the information when it is ready. 
<p />
We all agreed that one of the primary deficiencies is the GUI.  
Soichi may have some time in the future to work on GUI things and his intent to add <span class="twikiNewLink">AuthN<a href="/bin/edit/Documentation/AuthN?topicparent=Documentation.NetworkingDashboardAuthNZGroup" rel="nofollow" title="AuthN (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>/AuthZ is coupled to the GUI (since it will interact-with/depend-upon the GUI).    
Plan is to have everyone play with the old dashboard and perhaps use the OSG Networking discussion time-slot next week to continue the discussion.
<p />
